\section{Output pipeline (for contributors)}{

Every regression method in this package follows the same shape:
\enumerate{
\item The \verb{tula.<class>()} method extracts a coefficient matrix from the
fitted model, optionally applies a robust variance estimator via
\code{.resolve_robust_vcov()}, and builds two named numeric vectors for
the left / right header blocks.
\item It calls \code{build_coef_df()} to produce the canonical
row-per-coefficient data frame (factor grouping, label resolution,
intercept placement, optional reference rows).
\item It assembles a \code{tula_output} S3 object via \code{new_tula_output()} (or
one of the variant constructors for multinomial / multi-quantile
models) and attaches \verb{select=} state via \code{.attach_select()}.
\item The S3 print method (\code{\link[=print.tula_output]{print.tula_output()}}) formats the header with
\code{format_header()} and the coefficient table with
\code{format_coef_table()}, sharing a total width computed by
\code{compute_total_width()}.
}

To add a new model class, see the "Anatomy of a tula.\if{html}{\out{<class>}}() method"
comment block in \code{R/tula.R}. The shortest reference implementation is
\code{R/tula_lm.R}.
}

